&s;ecret treaty, which he knew to be nego|ciating
with the Porte, and of the light
in which Henry of Navarre was received,
M. St. Aubert recollected enough of
his former experience to be a&s;&s;ured, that
his gue&s;t could be only of an inferior
cla&s;s of politicians; and that, from the
