&s;plendour, than by a wi&s;h to make their
friends happy.</P>
<P>Emily returned, with delight, to the li|berty
which their pre&s;ence had re&s;train|ed,
to her books, her walks, and the ra|tional
conver&s;ation of M. and Madame St.
Aubert, who &s;eemed to rejoice, no le&s;s,
