&s;mugglers, who, in conveying prohibited
<PB N="118" REF="128">
goods over the Pyren&eacute;es, had been encoun|tered,
and conquered by a party of troops.</P>
<P>The travellers had lingered &s;o long among
the &s;ublimer &s;cenes of the&s;e mountains,
that they found them&s;elves entirely mi&s;ta|ken
in their calculation that they could reach
Montigny at &s;un-&s;et; but, as they wound
along the valley, they &s;aw, on a rude
Alpine bridge, that united two lofty crags
