<P>The elde&s;t of the children de&s;i&s;ted from
<PB N="136" REF="146">
his play, and &s;tood &s;till to ob&s;erve the
&s;trangers, while the younger continued his
little gambols, and tea&s;ed his brother to join
in them. St. Aubert looked with plea&s;ure
