the&s;e, and their lamented, mother; and he
&s;unk into a thoughtfulne&s;s, which Emily
ob&s;erving, &s;he immediately began to &s;ing
one of tho&s;e &s;imple and lively airs he was &s;o
fond of, and which &s;he knew how to give
with the mo&s;t captivating &s;weetne&s;s St.
Aubert &s;miled on her through his tears,
