<P>"Above all, my dear Emily," &s;aid he, "do
not indulge in the pride of fine feeling, the
romantic error of amiable minds. Tho&s;e,
<PB N="212" REF="222">
who really po&s;&s;e&s;s &s;en&s;ibility, ought early to
be taught, that it is a dangerous quality,
which is continually extracting the exce&s;s of
