&s;en&s;ibility, I am not an advocate for apa|thy.
At your age I &s;hould have &s;aid <HI>that</HI> is
a vice more hateful than all the errors of
&s;en&s;ibility, and I &s;ay &s;o &s;till. I call it a
<HI>vice,</HI> becau&s;e it leads to po&s;itive evil; in
this, however, it does no more than an ill|governed
&s;en&s;ibility, which, by &s;uch a rule,
